=============================================================
  OpenWrt Flash Guide - Ubiquiti NanoStation 5AC Loco
  AirOS WA.v8.7.21 -> OpenWrt 24.10.4
=============================================================

REQUIRED FILES (add these .bin files to this folder):
- WA.v8.7.21.48401.251212.0937.bin
- openwrt-24.10.4-ath79-generic-ubnt_nanostation-ac-loco-squashfs-sysupgrade.bin

PC NETWORK SETTINGS:
  IP: 192.168.1.2 | Subnet: 255.255.255.0 | Gateway: 192.168.1.1

=============================================================
PROCEDURE:
=============================================================

STEP 1 - SCP files to device (from PowerShell):
  scp -O WA.v8.7.21.48401.251212.0937.bin <user>@192.168.1.20:/tmp
  scp -O openwrt-24.10.4-ath79-generic-ubnt_nanostation-ac-loco-squashfs-sysupgrade.bin <user>@192.168.1.20:/tmp

STEP 2 - SSH in:
  ssh <user>@192.168.1.20
  (If host key error: ssh-keygen -R 192.168.1.20)

STEP 3 - Patch fwupdate binary (WA.v8.7.21 specific patch string):
  hexdump -Cv /bin/ubntbox | sed 's/12 e0 fe 27/00 00 00 00/g' | hexdump -R > /tmp/fwupdate.real
  chmod +x /tmp/fwupdate.real

  NOTE: For other firmware versions, find your patch string with:
  hexdump -Cv /bin/ubntbox | grep "fe 27"

STEP 4 - Create flash script (run each line individually):
  echo 'fwupdate.real -m /tmp/WA.v8.7.21.48401.251212.0937.bin -d &' > /tmp/flash.sh
  echo 'sleep 3' >> /tmp/flash.sh
  echo 'kill %1' >> /tmp/flash.sh
  echo 'sleep 1' >> /tmp/flash.sh
  echo 'dd if=/tmp/openwrt-24.10.4-ath79-generic-ubnt_nanostation-ac-loco-squashfs-sysupgrade.bin of=/dev/mtdblock2 bs=4096 count=256' >> /tmp/flash.sh
  echo 'dd if=/tmp/openwrt-24.10.4-ath79-generic-ubnt_nanostation-ac-loco-squashfs-sysupgrade.bin of=/dev/mtdblock3 bs=4096 skip=256' >> /tmp/flash.sh
  echo 'reboot' >> /tmp/flash.sh
  chmod +x /tmp/flash.sh

  Verify: cat /tmp/flash.sh

STEP 5 - Run it:
  /tmp/flash.sh
  (If reboot segfaults: echo b > /proc/sysrq-trigger)

STEP 6 - Ping until OpenWrt responds:
  ping -t 192.168.1.1

STEP 7 - Access OpenWrt:
  Browser: http://192.168.1.1
  Username: root | Password: (blank)
  Set password immediately: System -> Administration

=============================================================
IMPORTANT NOTES:
=============================================================
- /tmp clears on every reboot - re-SCP files if device reboots
- AirOS web UI: http://192.168.1.20 (before flash)
- OpenWrt web UI: http://192.168.1.1 (after flash)
- Use OpenWrt 24.10.3 or later to avoid read-only flash bug
- No soldering or UART required

=============================================================
HOW IT WORKS:
=============================================================
1. SIGNATURE BYPASS: We patch the branch instruction in ubntbox
   (12 e0 fe 27 on WA.v8.7.21) to NOPs so signature check always passes.

2. PARTITION UNLOCK + DD: We run fwupdate briefly to unlock MTD partitions,
   kill it before it finishes, then write OpenWrt directly with dd.

3. IMAGE SPLIT: Sysupgrade image is split across two partitions:
   - First 1MB (256 blocks) -> kernel (mtdblock2)
   - Remainder -> rootfs (mtdblock3)
=============================================================
